1. About STUDIE-8

This is my second "serious" attempt at making a quality "experimental"
MOD.  It is a bit more complex than the first attempt, "felt" which
only used three small samples in the entire piece.  "felt" can be found
in /mods/misc on the Aminet (which is probably where you found this
archive), at http://emrl.com/cmu, or on the emrl.com ftp site in
/pub/noise.

I was originally composing this piece on a Sunrize AD516, but about
25% of the way into it, i realized it would make an acceptable MOD.
The @{"samples" Link "SAMPLES"} were already 8bit, as well.

The piece is about 13 minutes long.

After being dropped from the AD516, It was composed with OctaMED v5,
in 8 channel mode, with the samples halved.  The loss of sound quality
in this particular case was minimal, or at the very least, irrelevant.

OctaMED Player is included in this archive.

